52// Defines for the TLS Cipher Suite Map.
53#define DEFINE_CIPHER_ENTRY_SSL3(name) \
54 { SSL3_CK_##name, "TLS_" #name }
55#define DEFINE_CIPHER_ENTRY_TLS1(name) \
56 { TLS1_CK_##name, "TLS_" #name }
57
58namespace rtc {
59namespace {
60// SRTP cipher suite table. |internal_name| is used to construct a
61// colon-separated profile strings which is needed by
62// SSL_CTX_set_tlsext_use_srtp().
63struct SrtpCipherMapEntry {
64 const char* internal_name;
65 const int id;
66};
67
68// Cipher name table. Maps internal OpenSSL cipher ids to the RFC name.
69struct SslCipherMapEntry {
70 uint32_t openssl_id;
71 const char* rfc_name;
72};
73

78 {"SRTP_AEAD_AES_128_GCM", SRTP_AEAD_AES_128_GCM},
79 {"SRTP_AEAD_AES_256_GCM", SRTP_AEAD_AES_256_GCM}};

146bool g_use_time_callback_for_testing = false;
147// Not used in production code. Actual time should be relative to Jan 1, 1970.
148void TimeCallbackForTesting(const SSL* ssl, struct timeval* out_clock) {
149 int64_t time = TimeNanos();
150 out_clock->tv_sec = time / kNumNanosecsPerSec;
151 out_clock->tv_usec = (time % kNumNanosecsPerSec) / kNumNanosecsPerMicrosec;
152}

157//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
158// StreamBIO
159//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
160
161static int stream_write(BIO* h, const char* buf, int num);
162static int stream_read(BIO* h, char* buf, int size);
163static int stream_puts(BIO* h, const char* str);
164static long stream_ctrl(BIO* h, int cmd, long arg1, void* arg2);
165static int stream_new(BIO* h);
166static int stream_free(BIO* data);
167
168static BIO_METHOD* BIO_stream_method() {
169 static BIO_METHOD* method = [] {
170 BIO_METHOD* method = BIO_meth_new(BIO_TYPE_BIO, "stream");
171 BIO_meth_set_write(method, stream_write);
172 BIO_meth_set_read(method, stream_read);
173 BIO_meth_set_puts(method, stream_puts);
174 BIO_meth_set_ctrl(method, stream_ctrl);
175 BIO_meth_set_create(method, stream_new);
176 BIO_meth_set_destroy(method, stream_free);
177 return method;
178 }();
179 return method;
180}
181
182static BIO* BIO_new_stream(StreamInterface* stream) {
183 BIO* ret = BIO_new(BIO_stream_method());
184 if (ret == nullptr) {
185 return nullptr;
186 }
187 BIO_set_data(ret, stream);
188 return ret;
189}
190
191// bio methods return 1 (or at least non-zero) on success and 0 on failure.
192
193static int stream_new(BIO* b) {
194 BIO_set_shutdown(b, 0);
195 BIO_set_init(b, 1);
196 BIO_set_data(b, 0);
197 return 1;
198}
199
200static int stream_free(BIO* b) {
201 if (b == nullptr) {
202 return 0;
203 }
204 return 1;
205}
206
207static int stream_read(BIO* b, char* out, int outl) {
208 if (!out) {
209 return -1;
210 }
211 StreamInterface* stream = static_cast<StreamInterface*>(BIO_get_data(b));
212 BIO_clear_retry_flags(b);
213 size_t read;
214 int error;
215 StreamResult result = stream->Read(out, outl, &read, &error);
216 if (result == SR_SUCCESS) {
217 return checked_cast<int>(read);
218 } else if (result == SR_BLOCK) {
219 BIO_set_retry_read(b);
220 }
221 return -1;
222}
223
224static int stream_write(BIO* b, const char* in, int inl) {
225 if (!in) {
226 return -1;
227 }
228 StreamInterface* stream = static_cast<StreamInterface*>(BIO_get_data(b));
229 BIO_clear_retry_flags(b);
230 size_t written;
231 int error;
232 StreamResult result = stream->Write(in, inl, &written, &error);
233 if (result == SR_SUCCESS) {
234 return checked_cast<int>(written);
235 } else if (result == SR_BLOCK) {
236 BIO_set_retry_write(b);
237 }
238 return -1;
239}
240
241static int stream_puts(BIO* b, const char* str) {
242 return stream_write(b, str, checked_cast<int>(strlen(str)));
243}
244
245static long stream_ctrl(BIO* b, int cmd, long num, void* ptr) {
246 switch (cmd) {
247 case BIO_CTRL_RESET:
248 return 0;
249 case BIO_CTRL_EOF: {
250 StreamInterface* stream = static_cast<StreamInterface*>(ptr);
251 // 1 means end-of-stream.
252 return (stream->GetState() == SS_CLOSED) ? 1 : 0;
253 }
254 case BIO_CTRL_WPENDING:
255 case BIO_CTRL_PENDING:
256 return 0;
257 case BIO_CTRL_FLUSH:
258 return 1;
259 case BIO_CTRL_DGRAM_QUERY_MTU:
260 // openssl defaults to mtu=256 unless we return something here.
261 // The handshake doesn't actually need to send packets above 1k,
262 // so this seems like a sensible value that should work in most cases.
263 // Webrtc uses the same value for video packets.
264 return 1200;
265 default:
266 return 0;
267 }
268}

274static std::atomic<bool> g_use_legacy_tls_protocols_override(false);
275static std::atomic<bool> g_allow_legacy_tls_protocols(false);
276
277void SetAllowLegacyTLSProtocols(const absl::optional<bool>& allow) {
278 g_use_legacy_tls_protocols_override.store(allow.has_value());
279 if (allow.has_value())
280 g_allow_legacy_tls_protocols.store(allow.value());
281}
282
283bool ShouldAllowLegacyTLSProtocols() {
284 // WEBKIT_WEBRTC: Remove DTL10 optional support.
285 return g_use_legacy_tls_protocols_override.load()
286 ? g_allow_legacy_tls_protocols.load()
287 : !webrtc::field_trial::IsDisabled("WebRTC-LegacyTlsProtocols");
288}

290OpenSSLStreamAdapter::OpenSSLStreamAdapter(
291 std::unique_ptr<StreamInterface> stream)
292 : stream_(std::move(stream)),
293 owner_(rtc::Thread::Current()),
294 state_(SSL_NONE),
295 role_(SSL_CLIENT),
296 ssl_read_needs_write_(false),
297 ssl_write_needs_read_(false),
298 ssl_(nullptr),
299 ssl_ctx_(nullptr),
300 ssl_mode_(SSL_MODE_TLS),
301 ssl_max_version_(SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_12),
302 // Default is to support legacy TLS protocols.
303 // This will be changed to default non-support in M82 or M83.
304 support_legacy_tls_protocols_flag_(ShouldAllowLegacyTLSProtocols()) {
305 stream_->SignalEvent.connect(this, &OpenSSLStreamAdapter::OnEvent);
306}

308OpenSSLStreamAdapter::~OpenSSLStreamAdapter() {
309 timeout_task_.Stop();
310 Cleanup(0);
311}

330bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SetPeerCertificateDigest(
331 const std::string& digest_alg,
332 const unsigned char* digest_val,
333 size_t digest_len,
334 SSLPeerCertificateDigestError* error) {
335 RTC_DCHECK(!peer_certificate_verified_);
336 RTC_DCHECK(!HasPeerCertificateDigest());
337 size_t expected_len;
338 if (error) {
339 *error = SSLPeerCertificateDigestError::NONE;
340 }
341
342 if (!OpenSSLDigest::GetDigestSize(digest_alg, &expected_len)) {
343 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unknown digest algorithm: " << digest_alg;
344 if (error) {
345 *error = SSLPeerCertificateDigestError::UNKNOWN_ALGORITHM;
346 }
347 return false;
348 }
349 if (expected_len != digest_len) {
350 if (error) {
351 *error = SSLPeerCertificateDigestError::INVALID_LENGTH;
352 }
353 return false;
354 }
355
356 peer_certificate_digest_value_.SetData(digest_val, digest_len);
357 peer_certificate_digest_algorithm_ = digest_alg;
358
359 if (!peer_cert_chain_) {
360 // Normal case, where the digest is set before we obtain the certificate
361 // from the handshake.
362 return true;
363 }
364
365 if (!VerifyPeerCertificate()) {
366 Error("SetPeerCertificateDigest", -1, SSL_AD_BAD_CERTIFICATE, false);
367 if (error) {
368 *error = SSLPeerCertificateDigestError::VERIFICATION_FAILED;
369 }
370 return false;
371 }
372
373 if (state_ == SSL_CONNECTED) {
374 // Post the event asynchronously to unwind the stack. The caller
375 // of ContinueSSL may be the same object listening for these
376 // events and may not be prepared for reentrancy.
377 PostEvent(SE_OPEN | SE_READ | SE_WRITE, 0);
378 }
379
380 return true;
381}
382
383std::string OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SslCipherSuiteToName(int cipher_suite) {
384#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
385 const SSL_CIPHER* ssl_cipher = SSL_get_cipher_by_value(cipher_suite);
386 if (!ssl_cipher) {
387 return std::string();
388 }
389 return SSL_CIPHER_standard_name(ssl_cipher);
390#else
391 for (const SslCipherMapEntry* entry = kSslCipherMap; entry->rfc_name;
392 ++entry) {
393 if (cipher_suite == static_cast<int>(entry->openssl_id)) {
394 return entry->rfc_name;
395 }
396 }
397 return std::string();
398#endif
399}
400
401bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::GetSslCipherSuite(int* cipher_suite) {
402 if (state_ != SSL_CONNECTED) {
403 return false;
404 }
405
406 const SSL_CIPHER* current_cipher = SSL_get_current_cipher(ssl_);
407 if (current_cipher == nullptr) {
408 return false;
409 }
410
411 *cipher_suite = static_cast<uint16_t>(SSL_CIPHER_get_id(current_cipher));
412 return true;
413}
414
415SSLProtocolVersion OpenSSLStreamAdapter::GetSslVersion() const {
416 if (state_ != SSL_CONNECTED) {
417 return SSL_PROTOCOL_NOT_GIVEN;
418 }
419
420 int ssl_version = SSL_version(ssl_);
421 if (ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS) {
422 if (ssl_version == DTLS1_VERSION) {
423 return SSL_PROTOCOL_DTLS_10;
424 } else if (ssl_version == DTLS1_2_VERSION) {
425 return SSL_PROTOCOL_DTLS_12;
426 }
427 } else {
428 if (ssl_version == TLS1_VERSION) {
429 return SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_10;
430 } else if (ssl_version == TLS1_1_VERSION) {
431 return SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_11;
432 } else if (ssl_version == TLS1_2_VERSION) {
433 return SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_12;
434 }
435 }
436
437 return SSL_PROTOCOL_NOT_GIVEN;
438}
439
440bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::GetSslVersionBytes(int* version) const {
441 if (state_ != SSL_CONNECTED) {
442 return false;
443 }
444 *version = SSL_version(ssl_);
445 return true;
446}

448// Key Extractor interface
449bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::ExportKeyingMaterial(const std::string& label,
450 const uint8_t* context,
451 size_t context_len,
452 bool use_context,
453 uint8_t* result,
454 size_t result_len) {
455 if (SSL_export_keying_material(ssl_, result, result_len, label.c_str(),
456 label.length(), const_cast<uint8_t*>(context),
457 context_len, use_context) != 1) {
458 return false;
459 }
460 return true;
461}
462
463bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SetDtlsSrtpCryptoSuites(
464 const std::vector<int>& ciphers) {
465 if (state_ != SSL_NONE) {
466 return false;
467 }
468
469 std::string internal_ciphers;
470 for (const int cipher : ciphers) {
471 bool found = false;
472 for (const auto& entry : kSrtpCipherMap) {
473 if (cipher == entry.id) {
474 found = true;
475 if (!internal_ciphers.empty()) {
476 internal_ciphers += ":";
477 }
478 internal_ciphers += entry.internal_name;
479 break;
480 }
481 }
482
483 if (!found) {
484 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Could not find cipher: " << cipher;
485 return false;
486 }
487 }
488
489 if (internal_ciphers.empty()) {
490 return false;
491 }
492
493 srtp_ciphers_ = internal_ciphers;
494 return true;
495}
496
497bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::GetDtlsSrtpCryptoSuite(int* crypto_suite) {
498 RTC_DCHECK(state_ == SSL_CONNECTED);
499 if (state_ != SSL_CONNECTED) {
500 return false;
501 }
502
503 const SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE* srtp_profile =
504 SSL_get_selected_srtp_profile(ssl_);
505
506 if (!srtp_profile) {
507 return false;
508 }
509
510 *crypto_suite = srtp_profile->id;
511 RTC_DCHECK(!SrtpCryptoSuiteToName(*crypto_suite).empty());
512 return true;
513}

515bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::IsTlsConnected() {
516 return state_ == SSL_CONNECTED;
517}
518
519int OpenSSLStreamAdapter::StartSSL() {
520 // Don't allow StartSSL to be called twice.
521 if (state_ != SSL_NONE) {
522 return -1;
523 }
524
525 if (stream_->GetState() != SS_OPEN) {
526 state_ = SSL_WAIT;
527 return 0;
528 }
529
530 state_ = SSL_CONNECTING;
531 if (int err = BeginSSL()) {
532 Error("BeginSSL", err, 0, false);
533 return err;
534 }
535
536 return 0;
537}

554//
555// StreamInterface Implementation
556//
557
558StreamResult OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Write(const void* data,
559 size_t data_len,
560 size_t* written,
561 int* error) {
562 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Write(" << data_len << ")";
563
564 switch (state_) {
565 case SSL_NONE:
566 // pass-through in clear text
567 return stream_->Write(data, data_len, written, error);
568
569 case SSL_WAIT:
570 case SSL_CONNECTING:
571 return SR_BLOCK;
572
573 case SSL_CONNECTED:
574 if (WaitingToVerifyPeerCertificate()) {
575 return SR_BLOCK;
576 }
577 break;
578
579 case SSL_ERROR:
580 case SSL_CLOSED:
581 default:
582 if (error) {
583 *error = ssl_error_code_;
584 }
585 return SR_ERROR;
586 }
587
588 // OpenSSL will return an error if we try to write zero bytes
589 if (data_len == 0) {
590 if (written) {
591 *written = 0;
592 }
593 return SR_SUCCESS;
594 }
595
596 ssl_write_needs_read_ = false;
597
598 int code = SSL_write(ssl_, data, checked_cast<int>(data_len));
599 int ssl_error = SSL_get_error(ssl_, code);
600 switch (ssl_error) {
601 case SSL_ERROR_NONE:
602 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- success";
603 RTC_DCHECK_GT(code, 0);
604 RTC_DCHECK_LE(code, data_len);
605 if (written)
606 *written = code;
607 return SR_SUCCESS;
608 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ:
609 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error want read";
610 ssl_write_needs_read_ = true;
611 return SR_BLOCK;
612 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE:
613 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error want write";
614 return SR_BLOCK;
615
616 case SSL_ERROR_ZERO_RETURN:
617 default:
618 Error("SSL_write", (ssl_error ? ssl_error : -1), 0, false);
619 if (error) {
620 *error = ssl_error_code_;
621 }
622 return SR_ERROR;
623 }
624 // not reached
625}
626
627StreamResult OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Read(void* data,
628 size_t data_len,
629 size_t* read,
630 int* error) {
631 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Read(" << data_len << ")";
632 switch (state_) {
633 case SSL_NONE:
634 // pass-through in clear text
635 return stream_->Read(data, data_len, read, error);
636 case SSL_WAIT:
637 case SSL_CONNECTING:
638 return SR_BLOCK;
639 case SSL_CONNECTED:
640 if (WaitingToVerifyPeerCertificate()) {
641 return SR_BLOCK;
642 }
643 break;
644 case SSL_CLOSED:
645 return SR_EOS;
646 case SSL_ERROR:
647 default:
648 if (error) {
649 *error = ssl_error_code_;
650 }
651 return SR_ERROR;
652 }
653
654 // Don't trust OpenSSL with zero byte reads
655 if (data_len == 0) {
656 if (read) {
657 *read = 0;
658 }
659 return SR_SUCCESS;
660 }
661
662 ssl_read_needs_write_ = false;
663
664 const int code = SSL_read(ssl_, data, checked_cast<int>(data_len));
665 const int ssl_error = SSL_get_error(ssl_, code);
666
667 switch (ssl_error) {
668 case SSL_ERROR_NONE:
669 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- success";
670 RTC_DCHECK_GT(code, 0);
671 RTC_DCHECK_LE(code, data_len);
672 if (read) {
673 *read = code;
674 }
675
676 if (ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS) {
677 // Enforce atomic reads -- this is a short read
678 unsigned int pending = SSL_pending(ssl_);
679
680 if (pending) {
681 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << " -- short DTLS read. flushing";
682 FlushInput(pending);
683 if (error) {
684 *error = SSE_MSG_TRUNC;
685 }
686 return SR_ERROR;
687 }
688 }
689 return SR_SUCCESS;
690 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ:
691 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error want read";
692 return SR_BLOCK;
693 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE:
694 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error want write";
695 ssl_read_needs_write_ = true;
696 return SR_BLOCK;
697 case SSL_ERROR_ZERO_RETURN:
698 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- remote side closed";
699 Close();
700 return SR_EOS;
701 default:
702 Error("SSL_read", (ssl_error ? ssl_error : -1), 0, false);
703 if (error) {
704 *error = ssl_error_code_;
705 }
706 return SR_ERROR;
707 }
708 // not reached
709}
710
711void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::FlushInput(unsigned int left) {
712 unsigned char buf[2048];
713
714 while (left) {
715 // This should always succeed
716 const int toread = (sizeof(buf) < left) ? sizeof(buf) : left;
717 const int code = SSL_read(ssl_, buf, toread);
718
719 const int ssl_error = SSL_get_error(ssl_, code);
720 RTC_DCHECK(ssl_error == SSL_ERROR_NONE);
721
722 if (ssl_error != SSL_ERROR_NONE) {
723 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error " << code;
724 Error("SSL_read", (ssl_error ? ssl_error : -1), 0, false);
725 return;
726 }
727
728 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- flushed " << code << " bytes";
729 left -= code;
730 }
731}
732
733void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Close() {
734 Cleanup(0);
735 RTC_DCHECK(state_ == SSL_CLOSED || state_ == SSL_ERROR);
736 // When we're closed at SSL layer, also close the stream level which
737 // performs necessary clean up. Otherwise, a new incoming packet after
738 // this could overflow the stream buffer.
739 stream_->Close();
740}
741
742StreamState OpenSSLStreamAdapter::GetState() const {
743 switch (state_) {
744 case SSL_WAIT:
745 case SSL_CONNECTING:
746 return SS_OPENING;
747 case SSL_CONNECTED:
748 if (WaitingToVerifyPeerCertificate()) {
749 return SS_OPENING;
750 }
751 return SS_OPEN;
752 default:
753 return SS_CLOSED;
754 }
755 // not reached
756}
757
758void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::OnEvent(StreamInterface* stream,
759 int events,
760 int err) {
761 int events_to_signal = 0;
762 int signal_error = 0;
763 RTC_DCHECK(stream == stream_.get());
764
765 if ((events & SE_OPEN)) {
766 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "OpenSSLStreamAdapter::OnEvent SE_OPEN";
767 if (state_ != SSL_WAIT) {
768 RTC_DCHECK(state_ == SSL_NONE);
769 events_to_signal |= SE_OPEN;
770 } else {
771 state_ = SSL_CONNECTING;
772 if (int err = BeginSSL()) {
773 Error("BeginSSL", err, 0, true);
774 return;
775 }
776 }
777 }
778
779 if ((events & (SE_READ | SE_WRITE))) {
780 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "OpenSSLStreamAdapter::OnEvent"
781 << ((events & SE_READ) ? " SE_READ" : "")
782 << ((events & SE_WRITE) ? " SE_WRITE" : "");
783 if (state_ == SSL_NONE) {
784 events_to_signal |= events & (SE_READ | SE_WRITE);
785 } else if (state_ == SSL_CONNECTING) {
786 if (int err = ContinueSSL()) {
787 Error("ContinueSSL", err, 0, true);
788 return;
789 }
790 } else if (state_ == SSL_CONNECTED) {
791 if (((events & SE_READ) && ssl_write_needs_read_) ||
792 (events & SE_WRITE)) {
793 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- onStreamWriteable";
794 events_to_signal |= SE_WRITE;
795 }
796 if (((events & SE_WRITE) && ssl_read_needs_write_) ||
797 (events & SE_READ)) {
798 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- onStreamReadable";
799 events_to_signal |= SE_READ;
800 }
801 }
802 }
803
804 if ((events & SE_CLOSE)) {
805 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "OpenSSLStreamAdapter::OnEvent(SE_CLOSE, " << err
806 << ")";
807 Cleanup(0);
808 events_to_signal |= SE_CLOSE;
809 // SE_CLOSE is the only event that uses the final parameter to OnEvent().
810 RTC_DCHECK(signal_error == 0);
811 signal_error = err;
812 }
813
814 if (events_to_signal) {
815 // Note that the adapter presents itself as the origin of the stream events,
816 // since users of the adapter may not recognize the adapted object.
817 SignalEvent(this, events_to_signal, signal_error);
818 }
819}
820
821void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::PostEvent(int events, int err) {
822 owner_->PostTask(webrtc::ToQueuedTask(
823 task_safety_, [this, events, err]() { SignalEvent(this, events, err); }));
824}
825
826void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SetTimeout(int delay_ms) {
827 // We need to accept 0 delay here as well as >0 delay, because
828 // DTLSv1_get_timeout seems to frequently return 0 ms.
829 RTC_DCHECK_GE(delay_ms, 0);
830 RTC_DCHECK(!timeout_task_.Running());
831
832 timeout_task_ = webrtc::RepeatingTaskHandle::DelayedStart(
833 owner_, webrtc::TimeDelta::Millis(delay_ms),
834 [flag = task_safety_.flag(), this]() {
835 if (flag->alive()) {
836 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "DTLS timeout expired";
837 timeout_task_.Stop();
838 DTLSv1_handle_timeout(ssl_);
839 ContinueSSL();
840 } else {
841 RTC_NOTREACHED();
842 }
843 // This callback will never run again (stopped above).
844 return webrtc::TimeDelta::PlusInfinity();
845 });
846}
847
848int OpenSSLStreamAdapter::BeginSSL() {
849 RTC_DCHECK(state_ == SSL_CONNECTING);
850 // The underlying stream has opened.
851 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "BeginSSL with peer.";
852
853 BIO* bio = nullptr;
854
855 // First set up the context.
856 RTC_DCHECK(ssl_ctx_ == nullptr);
857 ssl_ctx_ = SetupSSLContext();
858 if (!ssl_ctx_) {
859 return -1;
860 }
861
862 bio = BIO_new_stream(stream_.get());
863 if (!bio) {
864 return -1;
865 }
866
867 ssl_ = SSL_new(ssl_ctx_);
868 if (!ssl_) {
869 BIO_free(bio);
870 return -1;
871 }
872
873 SSL_set_app_data(ssl_, this);
874
875 SSL_set_bio(ssl_, bio, bio); // the SSL object owns the bio now.
876 if (ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS) {
877#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
878 DTLSv1_set_initial_timeout_duration(ssl_, dtls_handshake_timeout_ms_);
879#else
880 // Enable read-ahead for DTLS so whole packets are read from internal BIO
881 // before parsing. This is done internally by BoringSSL for DTLS.
882 SSL_set_read_ahead(ssl_, 1);
883#endif
884 }
885
886 SSL_set_mode(ssl_, SSL_MODE_ENABLE_PARTIAL_WRITE |
887 SSL_MODE_ACCEPT_MOVING_WRITE_BUFFER);
888
889 // Do the connect
890 return ContinueSSL();
891}
892
893int OpenSSLStreamAdapter::ContinueSSL() {
894 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "ContinueSSL";
895 RTC_DCHECK(state_ == SSL_CONNECTING);
896
897 // Clear the DTLS timer
898 timeout_task_.Stop();
899
900 const int code = (role_ == SSL_CLIENT) ? SSL_connect(ssl_) : SSL_accept(ssl_);
901 const int ssl_error = SSL_get_error(ssl_, code);
902
903 switch (ssl_error) {
904 case SSL_ERROR_NONE:
905 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- success";
906 // By this point, OpenSSL should have given us a certificate, or errored
907 // out if one was missing.
908 RTC_DCHECK(peer_cert_chain_ || !GetClientAuthEnabled());
909
910 state_ = SSL_CONNECTED;
911 if (!WaitingToVerifyPeerCertificate()) {
912 // We have everything we need to start the connection, so signal
913 // SE_OPEN. If we need a client certificate fingerprint and don't have
914 // it yet, we'll instead signal SE_OPEN in SetPeerCertificateDigest.
915 //
916 // TODO(deadbeef): Post this event asynchronously to unwind the stack.
917 // The caller of ContinueSSL may be the same object listening for these
918 // events and may not be prepared for reentrancy.
919 // PostEvent(SE_OPEN | SE_READ | SE_WRITE, 0);
920 SignalEvent(this, SE_OPEN | SE_READ | SE_WRITE, 0);
921 }
922 break;
923
924 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ: {
925 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error want read";
926 struct timeval timeout;
927 if (DTLSv1_get_timeout(ssl_, &timeout)) {
928 int delay = timeout.tv_sec * 1000 + timeout.tv_usec / 1000;
929 SetTimeout(delay);
930 }
931 } break;
932
933 case SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE:
934 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error want write";
935 break;
936
937 case SSL_ERROR_ZERO_RETURN:
938 default:
939 SSLHandshakeError ssl_handshake_err = SSLHandshakeError::UNKNOWN;
940 int err_code = ERR_peek_last_error();
941 if (err_code != 0 && ERR_GET_REASON(err_code) == SSL_R_NO_SHARED_CIPHER) {
942 ssl_handshake_err = SSLHandshakeError::INCOMPATIBLE_CIPHERSUITE;
943 }
944 RTC_DLOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " -- error " << code << ", " << err_code << ", "
945 << ERR_GET_REASON(err_code);
946 SignalSSLHandshakeError(ssl_handshake_err);
947 return (ssl_error != 0) ? ssl_error : -1;
948 }
949
950 return 0;
951}
952
953void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Error(const char* context,
954 int err,
955 uint8_t alert,
956 bool signal) {
957 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Error(" << context << ", "
958 << err << ", " << static_cast<int>(alert) << ")";
959 state_ = SSL_ERROR;
960 ssl_error_code_ = err;
961 Cleanup(alert);
962 if (signal) {
963 SignalEvent(this, SE_CLOSE, err);
964 }
965}
966
967void OpenSSLStreamAdapter::Cleanup(uint8_t alert) {
968 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Cleanup";
969
970 if (state_ != SSL_ERROR) {
971 state_ = SSL_CLOSED;
972 ssl_error_code_ = 0;
973 }
974
975 if (ssl_) {
976 int ret;
977// SSL_send_fatal_alert is only available in BoringSSL.
978#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
979 if (alert) {
980 ret = SSL_send_fatal_alert(ssl_, alert);
981 if (ret < 0) {
982 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SSL_send_fatal_alert failed, error = "
983 << SSL_get_error(ssl_, ret);
984 }
985 } else {
986#endif
987 ret = SSL_shutdown(ssl_);
988 if (ret < 0) {
989 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
990 << "SSL_shutdown failed, error = " << SSL_get_error(ssl_, ret);
991 }
992#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
993 }
994#endif
995 SSL_free(ssl_);
996 ssl_ = nullptr;
997 }
998 if (ssl_ctx_) {
999 SSL_CTX_free(ssl_ctx_);
1000 ssl_ctx_ = nullptr;
1001 }
1002 identity_.reset();
1003 peer_cert_chain_.reset();
1004
1005 // Clear the DTLS timer
1006 timeout_task_.Stop();
1007}
1008
1009SSL_CTX* OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SetupSSLContext() {
1010#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
1011 // If X509 objects aren't used, we can use these methods to avoid
1012 // linking the sizable crypto/x509 code, using CRYPTO_BUFFER instead.
1013 SSL_CTX* ctx =
1014 SSL_CTX_new(ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS_with_buffers_method()
1015 : TLS_with_buffers_method());
1016#else
1017 SSL_CTX* ctx =
1018 SSL_CTX_new(ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS_method() : TLS_method());
1019#endif
1020 if (ctx == nullptr) {
1021 return nullptr;
1022 }
1023
1024 if (support_legacy_tls_protocols_flag_) {
1025 // TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/10261): Completely remove this branch in
1026 // M84.
1027 SSL_CTX_set_min_proto_version(
1028 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_VERSION : TLS1_VERSION);
1029 switch (ssl_max_version_) {
1030 case SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_10:
1031 SSL_CTX_set_max_proto_version(
1032 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_VERSION : TLS1_VERSION);
1033 break;
1034 case SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_11:
1035 SSL_CTX_set_max_proto_version(
1036 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_VERSION : TLS1_1_VERSION);
1037 break;
1038 case SSL_PROTOCOL_TLS_12:
1039 default:
1040#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
1041 SSL_CTX_set_min_proto_version(
1042 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_2_VERSION : TLS1_2_VERSION);
1043#endif
1044 SSL_CTX_set_max_proto_version(
1045 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_2_VERSION : TLS1_2_VERSION);
1046 break;
1047 }
1048 } else {
1049 // TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/10261): Make this the default in M84.
1050 SSL_CTX_set_min_proto_version(
1051 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_2_VERSION : TLS1_2_VERSION);
1052 SSL_CTX_set_max_proto_version(
1053 ctx, ssl_mode_ == SSL_MODE_DTLS ? DTLS1_2_VERSION : TLS1_2_VERSION);
1054 }
1055
1056#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
1057 // SSL_CTX_set_current_time_cb is only supported in BoringSSL.
1058 if (g_use_time_callback_for_testing) {
1059 SSL_CTX_set_current_time_cb(ctx, &TimeCallbackForTesting);
1060 }
1061 SSL_CTX_set0_buffer_pool(ctx, openssl::GetBufferPool());
1062#endif
1063
1064 if (identity_ && !identity_->ConfigureIdentity(ctx)) {
1065 SSL_CTX_free(ctx);
1066 return nullptr;
1067 }
1068
1069#if !defined(NDEBUG)
1070 SSL_CTX_set_info_callback(ctx, OpenSSLAdapter::SSLInfoCallback);
1071#endif
1072
1073 int mode = SSL_VERIFY_PEER;
1074 if (GetClientAuthEnabled()) {
1075 // Require a certificate from the client.
1076 // Note: Normally this is always true in production, but it may be disabled
1077 // for testing purposes (e.g. SSLAdapter unit tests).
1078 mode |= SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT;
1079 }
1080
1081 // Configure a custom certificate verification callback to check the peer
1082 // certificate digest.
1083#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
1084 // Use CRYPTO_BUFFER version of the callback if building with BoringSSL.
1085 SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify(ctx, mode, SSLVerifyCallback);
1086#else
1087 // Note the second argument to SSL_CTX_set_verify is to override individual
1088 // errors in the default verification logic, which is not what we want here.
1089 SSL_CTX_set_verify(ctx, mode, nullptr);
1090 SSL_CTX_set_cert_verify_callback(ctx, SSLVerifyCallback, nullptr);
1091#endif
1092
1093 // Select list of available ciphers. Note that !SHA256 and !SHA384 only
1094 // remove HMAC-SHA256 and HMAC-SHA384 cipher suites, not GCM cipher suites
1095 // with SHA256 or SHA384 as the handshake hash.
1096 // This matches the list of SSLClientSocketOpenSSL in Chromium.
1097 SSL_CTX_set_cipher_list(
1098 ctx, "DEFAULT:!NULL:!aNULL:!SHA256:!SHA384:!aECDH:!AESGCM+AES256:!aPSK");
1099
1100 if (!srtp_ciphers_.empty()) {
1101 if (SSL_CTX_set_tlsext_use_srtp(ctx, srtp_ciphers_.c_str())) {
1102 SSL_CTX_free(ctx);
1103 return nullptr;
1104 }
1105 }
1106
1107 return ctx;
1108}
1109
1110bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::VerifyPeerCertificate() {
1111 if (!HasPeerCertificateDigest() || !peer_cert_chain_ ||
1112 !peer_cert_chain_->GetSize()) {
1113 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Missing digest or peer certificate.";
1114 return false;
1115 }
1116
1117 unsigned char digest[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
1118 size_t digest_length;
1119 if (!peer_cert_chain_->Get(0).ComputeDigest(
1120 peer_certificate_digest_algorithm_, digest, sizeof(digest),
1121 &digest_length)) {
1122 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to compute peer cert digest.";
1123 return false;
1124 }
1125
1126 Buffer computed_digest(digest, digest_length);
1127 if (computed_digest != peer_certificate_digest_value_) {
1128 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1129 << "Rejected peer certificate due to mismatched digest.";
1130 return false;
1131 }
1132 // Ignore any verification error if the digest matches, since there is no
1133 // value in checking the validity of a self-signed cert issued by untrusted
1134 // sources.
1135 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Accepted peer certificate.";
1136 peer_certificate_verified_ = true;
1137 return true;
1138}

1140std::unique_ptr<SSLCertChain> OpenSSLStreamAdapter::GetPeerSSLCertChain()
1141 const {
1142 return peer_cert_chain_ ? peer_cert_chain_->Clone() : nullptr;
1143}

1145#ifdef OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
1146enum ssl_verify_result_t OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SSLVerifyCallback(
1147 SSL* ssl,
1148 uint8_t* out_alert) {
1149 // Get our OpenSSLStreamAdapter from the context.
1150 OpenSSLStreamAdapter* stream =
1151 reinterpret_cast<OpenSSLStreamAdapter*>(SSL_get_app_data(ssl));
1152 const STACK_OF(CRYPTO_BUFFER)* chain = SSL_get0_peer_certificates(ssl);
1153 // Creates certificate chain.
1154 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<SSLCertificate>> cert_chain;
1155 for (CRYPTO_BUFFER* cert : chain) {
1156 cert_chain.emplace_back(new BoringSSLCertificate(bssl::UpRef(cert)));
1157 }
1158 stream->peer_cert_chain_.reset(new SSLCertChain(std::move(cert_chain)));
1159
1160 // If the peer certificate digest isn't known yet, we'll wait to verify
1161 // until it's known, and for now just return a success status.
1162 if (stream->peer_certificate_digest_algorithm_.empty()) {
1163 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Waiting to verify certificate until digest is known.";
1164 // TODO(deadbeef): Use ssl_verify_retry?
1165 return ssl_verify_ok;
1166 }
1167
1168 if (!stream->VerifyPeerCertificate()) {
1169 return ssl_verify_invalid;
1170 }
1171
1172 return ssl_verify_ok;
1173}
1174#else // OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL
1175int OpenSSLStreamAdapter::SSLVerifyCallback(X509_STORE_CTX* store, void* arg) {
1176 // Get our SSL structure and OpenSSLStreamAdapter from the store.
1177 SSL* ssl = reinterpret_cast<SSL*>(
1178 X509_STORE_CTX_get_ex_data(store, SSL_get_ex_data_X509_STORE_CTX_idx()));
1179 OpenSSLStreamAdapter* stream =
1180 reinterpret_cast<OpenSSLStreamAdapter*>(SSL_get_app_data(ssl));
1181
1182 // Record the peer's certificate.
1183 X509* cert = X509_STORE_CTX_get0_cert(store);
1184 stream->peer_cert_chain_.reset(
1185 new SSLCertChain(std::make_unique<OpenSSLCertificate>(cert)));
1186
1187 // If the peer certificate digest isn't known yet, we'll wait to verify
1188 // until it's known, and for now just return a success status.
1189 if (stream->peer_certificate_digest_algorithm_.empty()) {
1190 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Waiting to verify certificate until digest is known.";
1191 return 1;
1192 }
1193
1194 if (!stream->VerifyPeerCertificate()) {
1195 X509_STORE_CTX_set_error(store, X509_V_ERR_CERT_REJECTED);
1196 return 0;
1197 }
1198
1199 return 1;
1200}
1201#endif // !OPENSSL_IS_BORINGSSL

1211#define CDEF(X) \
1212 { static_cast<uint16_t>(TLS1_CK_##X & 0xffff), "TLS_" #X }
1213
1214struct cipher_list {
1215 uint16_t cipher;
1216 const char* cipher_str;
1217};
1218
1219// TODO(torbjorng): Perhaps add more cipher suites to these lists.
1220static const cipher_list OK_RSA_ciphers[] = {
1221 CDEF(ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA),
1222 CDEF(ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA),
1223 CDEF(ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256),
1224#ifdef TLS1_CK_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA256
1225 CDEF(ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA256),
1226#endif
1227#ifdef TLS1_CK_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
1228 CDEF(ECDHE_RSA_WITH_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256),
1229#endif
1230};
1231
1232static const cipher_list OK_ECDSA_ciphers[] = {
1233 CDEF(ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_CBC_SHA),
1234 CDEF(ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_CBC_SHA),
1235 CDEF(ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256),
1236#ifdef TLS1_CK_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA256
1237 CDEF(ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA256),
1238#endif
1239#ifdef TLS1_CK_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
1240 CDEF(ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256),
1241#endif
1242};
1243#undef CDEF
1244
1245bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::IsAcceptableCipher(int cipher, KeyType key_type) {
1246 if (key_type == KT_RSA) {
1247 for (const cipher_list& c : OK_RSA_ciphers) {
1248 if (cipher == c.cipher) {
1249 return true;
1250 }
1251 }
1252 }
1253
1254 if (key_type == KT_ECDSA) {
1255 for (const cipher_list& c : OK_ECDSA_ciphers) {
1256 if (cipher == c.cipher) {
1257 return true;
1258 }
1259 }
1260 }
1261
1262 return false;
1263}
1264
1265bool OpenSSLStreamAdapter::IsAcceptableCipher(const std::string& cipher,
1266 KeyType key_type) {
1267 if (key_type == KT_RSA) {
1268 for (const cipher_list& c : OK_RSA_ciphers) {
1269 if (cipher == c.cipher_str) {
1270 return true;
1271 }
1272 }
1273 }
1274
1275 if (key_type == KT_ECDSA) {
1276 for (const cipher_list& c : OK_ECDSA_ciphers) {
1277 if (cipher == c.cipher_str) {
1278 return true;
1279 }
1280 }
1281 }
1282
1283 return false;
1284}
